1) do not need direct disclosure or proof
	A) just a reasonable suspicion
		I) if you suspect, report
		II) direct disclosure also must be reported
			a) 14 or older abuser must report

2) how to make a report
	A) make a repoprt by phone is required
		I) as soon as possible
		II) then send a SCAR form
			a) Suspected Child Abuse Report
		III) no anonymous reporting
			a) I don't like that, that should be changed
		IV) mandatory reporter reports it
			a) even if the supervisor disagrees
